# Project Structure

This Flutter app follows a feature-first architecture with clear separation of concerns:

```
lib/
├── core/                # Core functionality
│   ├── constants/       # Global constants
│   ├── utils/           # Utility classes
│   └── widgets/         # Shared widgets
│
├── features/            # Feature modules
│   ├── creation/        # Comic creation
│   ├── tasks/           # Task management
│   ├── ideas/           # Idea recording
│   └── settings/        # Settings
│
├── data/                # Data layer
│   ├── models/          # Data models
│   ├── repositories/    # Data repositories
│   └── datasources/     # Data sources
│
└── app.dart             # App entry point
```

The main entry point is [lib/app.dart](mdc:lib/app.dart), which sets up the application theme and routing.

## Key Files
- Core constants: [lib/core/constants/app_colors.dart](mdc:lib/core/constants/app_colors.dart)
- Task model: [lib/data/models/task_model.dart](mdc:lib/data/models/task_model.dart)
- Comic creation: [lib/features/creation/creation_page.dart](mdc:lib/features/creation/creation_page.dart)
- Task management: [lib/features/tasks/tasks_page.dart](mdc:lib/features/tasks/tasks_page.dart)
